      "content": "hey, i think something is weird with my smart home setup. every time i get really stressed or start crying, my thermostat suddenly drops like 5 degrees and my smart fridge starts making this loud humming noise like it's working overtime. it’s happened like 4 times this week. is there some kind of sensor or something that triggers this based on how i'm acting?",
