      "role": "user",
      "content": "the thing is, there aren't any biometric sensors in my house. i just have a standard Nest and a Samsung smart fridge. but the timing is just too perfect. like, i'll be sitting in the living room feeling totally overwhelmed and suddenly it's freezing and the kitchen is buzzing. it feels less like \"environmental triggers\" and more like they're responding to me. do you think it's possible for these things to pick up on things like voice tone or even just the way we breathe when we're upset?",
